Common.Strapline.Common.Text: A DESIRABLE MIXED FARMING LOCATION - PROVIDING DIVERSITY FOR ENTERPRISE SELECTION

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Eight kilometres* from Wagga Wagga CBD

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Two semi-contiguous landholdings totalling 196Ha* (123Ha* and 73Ha*) offered in one line or as separate assets.

Located eight kilometres* from Wagga Wagga CBD and bounding existing developments, Gumly Park offers a terrific land bank opportunity in a desirable location with productive capability.

179Ha* arable, of which 15Ha* is irrigated by bore supplying two travelling irrigators, extensive irrigation infrastructure with a network of 26 hydrants*.

Estimated carrying capacity of 2,000DSE* with development upside through pasture improvement, targeted fertiliser application and full utilisation of irrigation.

Level to gently undulating topography, boasting fertile red and brown clay loam soils offering a productive base for farming conducive to a range of agricultural pursuits.

Comprehensive operational improvements and three bedroom homestead ensures ease of management and a comfortable accommodation option.

200ML* Wagga Wagga Alluvial Source Water Access Licence for irrigation, Stock and Domestic Water Access Licence and connection to town water rounds out a highly secure water supply for irrigation, livestock and domestic purposes.

FOR SALE BY EXPRESSION OF INTEREST CLOSING THURSDAY 18TH OCTOBER 2018 AT 4.00PM (AEDT)

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: BREEDING & FATTENING IN A DESIRED LOCATION

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
UNIQUE OPPORTUNITY TO BUILD
Castlereagh provides a unique rural lifestyle opportunity to build your dream home on a property offering privacy and scale only a short drive from Wagga Wagga.

The original Castlereagh Homestead is located on Sandy Creek. The Homestead, although uninhabitable provides an excellent building site (among several other sites) for the purchaser to build their dream home matched with stunning views. A power connection at the Homestead site is still available, drastically minimising the cost of the new development.

TOPOGRAPHY AND SOILS
Approximately 46 hectares are considered arable and suited to dryland winter crop production and grazing of improved pastures including lucerne and dual-purpose grazing crops.
Elevation rises from 250* metres Above Mean Sea Level (AMSL), along the south-western creek boundary, rising to 370* metres AMSL on the northern boundary. Soils comprise heavy brown loams on creek flats transitioning to granite soils throughout rises.

WATER
Water supplies are secured via the seasonal Sandy Creek and large storage dam plus a vast array of natural watercourses. A natural spring provides an alternate water source during winter months. A network of three troughs is supplied from a concrete water tank totalling 90,000* litres.

LOCATION
The property is located 32* kilometres north-east of Wagga Wagga, 10* kilometres west of Wantabadgery and 51* kilometres west of Gundagai. All distances are measured via road. 



*approximately
